<p class="latin1" data-index="4945"><span class="label" data-index="4946"><b data-index="4947">c.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> On December 31, before computing depreciation expense on Machine C, the management of Eshkol, Inc. decided the useful life remaining from January 1, 2021, was 10 years.</p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="4948"><span class="label" data-index="4949"><b data-index="4950">d.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> On December 31, it was discovered that a machine purchased in 2020 had been expensed completely in that year. This machine cost $28,000 and has a useful life of 10 years and no salvage value. Management has decided to use the double-declining-balance method for this machine, which can be referred to as “Machine E.”</p>
<h4 data-index="4951"><span class="red" data-index="4952">Instructions</span></h4>
<p data-index="4953">Prepare the necessary correcting entries for the year 2021. Record the appropriate depreciation expense on the above-mentioned machines. No entry is necessary for Machine D.</p>
<p data-index="4954"><b data-index="4955"><span class="codeColorBlue2" data-index="4956">P11.4</span></b> <span class="red" data-index="4957">(LO <a href="#lo_1" data-index="4958" data-section-index="21" data-section-idref="lo_1" data-target-data-index="124">1</a>, <a href="#lo_2" data-index="4959" data-section-index="21" data-section-idref="lo_2" data-target-data-index="976">2</a>)</span> <b data-index="4960">(Depreciation and Error Analysis)</b> A depreciation schedule for semi-trucks of Ichiro Manufacturing Company was requested by your auditor soon after December 31, 2021, showing the additions, retirements, depreciation, and other data affecting the income of the company in the 4-year period 2018 to 2021, inclusive. The following data were ­ascertained.</p>
